The paper proposes a method for generating pseudo random numbers of q-Gaussian random variables based on deterministic chaotic map dynamics. This involves the use of piecewise linear maps and unit circle maps. The paper also conducts statistical tests to validate the generated q-Gaussian samples. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), as the paper deals with generating random numbers using mathematical methods. The second likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper involves the generation of random variables. The third likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper deals with deterministic chaotic map dynamics. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper involves the use of maps and piecewise linear functions. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper involves the generation of random variables, which is a common task in machine learning.
